    "image_text_tLNKi3": {
      "type": "image_text",
      "blocks": {
        "bl_text_EXxjCm": {
          "type": "bl_text",
          "settings": {
            "col_dk": "12",
            "col_tb": "12",
            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>Tribal Drape #1: The Santhali Wrap</h2><p>Inspired by the Santal women of Jharkhand and Odisha, this drape doesn’t require a petticoat. You wrap the saree around your chest, cross it under your arms, tie a secure knot at the back, and let the rest flow around your waist. Simple. Secure. Sexy, without trying.</p><p>I paired it with silver tribal jewelry and skipped the blouse for full authenticity. It felt bold — but not forced. Like I was channeling something ancient and fierce.</p><p>Learn how to drape through this video: </p>",
